.:: Puzzle 7x4-Level-7-11::.
There 4 different types of food: cucumber, garlic, grapes, lime
The people's birthday is in 4 different months: march, september, january, april
The people have 4 different jobs:  firefighter, journalist, photographer, writer
City: hannover, new-york, san-francisco, edinburgh
4 different pets are kept: fish, hedgehog, pony, rat
There are 4 different favourite beverages: lemonade, fanta, coffee, iced-tea
4 different brands of cigars are smoked: baccarat, fonseca, cain, old-henry
 1. the person eating garlic is on the left or right of the person who's birthday is in april##3
 2. the fonseca-smoker is somewhere to the right of the journalist##5
 3. the person who's birthday is in january is not the person traveling to hannover##6
 4. the person eating cucumber is on the right of the owner of the hedgehog##1
 5. the photographer is somewhere to the left of the writer##5
 6. the photographer is not the baccarat-smoker##6
 7. the firefighter is somewhere to the right of the person who's birthday is in march##5
 8. the owner of the pony is on the left or right of the person drinking lemonade##3
 9. the owner of the pony is somewhere between the firefighter and the owner of the rat##7
10. the journalist is somewhere to the right of the writer##5
11. the person who's birthday is in march is on the left or right of the owner of the rat##3
12. the baccarat-smoker is on the left of the person who's birthday is in april##1
13. the person eating lime is somewhere to the right of the person traveling to hannover##5
14. the firefighter is on the right of the person traveling to hannover##1
15. the person traveling to san-francisco is on the right of the owner of the hedgehog##1
16. the person drinking fanta is on the right of the person who's birthday is in september##1
17. the cain-smoker is on the left or right of the person drinking lemonade##3
18. the person traveling to new-york is on the left or right of the old-henry-smoker##3
19. the person who's birthday is in march is the person who's birthday is in march##1
20. the person eating grapes is on the left of the owner of the rat##1
21. the person eating garlic is somewhere to the right of the person drinking lemonade##5
22. the person drinking iced-tea is on the left of the person eating lime##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |      1       |     2     |     3      |      4      |
| Food          | grapes       | cucumber  | garlic     | lime        |
| Birthday         | march      | january | september | april     |
| Job           | photographer | writer    | journalist | firefighter |
| City   | new-york     | san-francisco   | hannover     | edinburgh     |
| Pet           | hedgehog     | rat       | pony       | fish        |
| Beverage         | coffee      | lemonade   | iced-tea     | fanta    |
| Cigar     | cain         | old-henry     | baccarat        | fonseca  |

